  "title": "Core Concepts of Exploring Elements of Gang Culture",
  "lessonText": "This section delves into the foundational elements that define gang culture.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• Gang culture is a complex social phenomenon involving groups that share common interests, often associated with criminal activities.\n• Key characteristics of gang culture include:\n  - Identity: Gangs often create a sense of belonging among members.\n  - Territory: Many gangs claim specific geographic areas.\n  - Symbols: Gangs use unique symbols and colors to signify affiliation.\n  - Codes of Conduct: Gangs have rules that govern behavior and interactions.\n• The 'Defining Gang Culture Walkthrough' video provides a comprehensive overview of these core characteristics.\n• Engage with the 'Challenge: Fill in the blanks' activity to reinforce your understanding of these concepts, using clues from the Learning Cards and Concept Breakdown."
  }
}
